<div class="calendaria chat-release">
  <div class="release-header">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-calendar"></i>
    <strong>{{localize "CALENDARIA.Release.Title" version=version}}</strong>
  </div>

  <div class="release-body">
    <p class="release-patreon">
      <strong><a href="https://www.patreon.com/3deathsaves" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i
            class="fa-brands fa-patreon"></i> Now on Patreon!</a></strong>
    </p>

    <h4>New Features</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Cinematic overlay picks up the active theme so pill, progress bar, festival cards, and event highlights recolor to match themed worlds</li>
      <li>Sun, moon, and sky in the cinematic track the real in-world time between the skip's start and end hours</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Bug Fixes</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><code>[namedWeek]</code> and <code>[namedWeekAbbr]</code> format tokens resolve against the calendar's named weeks, honoring week type and the Repeat flag</li>
      <li>Cinematic pill fades in once the starting date is populated, so the first panel no longer flashes blank</li>
      <li>Computed seasonal notes and legacy migrations resolve astronomical anchors through season-type metadata, so equinox/solstice triggers fire on the right day</li>
      <li>Custom format tokens that resolve to empty strings render the literal token instead of vanishing</li>
      <li>Equinox and solstice festivals land on the correct date for month-anchored calendars like Golarion and Pact-Standard</li>
      <li>First cinematic frame seeds the date label immediately, and a malformed keyframe no longer crashes the animation loop</li>
      <li>Theme preset dropdown and Customize button unlock the moment Force Theme is set back to None</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Changes</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Seasons left without a Seasonal Type are skipped by astronomical anchors; the season editor hint calls this out</li>
    </ul>

  </div>

  <a class="open-note" href="{{repoUrl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
    <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up-right-from-square"></i> {{localize "CALENDARIA.Release.ReleaseNotes"}}
  </a>
</div>
